%% Sequence Diagram: Session / Chat Flow
%% Chapter 6, Section 6.4
%% UC-04: Conduct Interactive Practice Session
%%
%% Validated against PROJECT/crackint-frontend (SessionChatView, HomeChatInput) + PROJECT/crackint-backend/app/api/session/route.py
%%
%% Primary UI flow uses ONE unified endpoint:
%%   POST /api/v1/sessions/{session_id}/chat  (body: { content, prefer_difficulty? })
%% It stores the user turn and runs the session QA agent in-process: first question, classify/redirect,
%% evaluate_answer, generate_next_question, tutor replies — as applicable — then returns new_messages.
%%
%% Also implemented (not used by main chat UI): POST .../messages (raw append), POST .../next-question,
%% POST .../evaluate-answer, POST .../send — see route.py for behaviour.
%%
%% LLM: OPENAI_API_KEY from PROJECT/crackint-backend/app/config.py

sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Frontend as Next.js Frontend
    participant API as FastAPI API
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant LLM as LLM (OpenAI API)

    User->>Frontend: Start new session (résumé + job selected, or tutor mode from home)
    Frontend->>API: POST /api/v1/sessions (resume_id, job_posting_id, mode)
    API->>DB: INSERT PrepSession
    DB-->>API: session_id
    API-->>Frontend: PrepSession
    Frontend->>API: GET /api/v1/sessions/{id}/with-messages
    API->>DB: SELECT session + messages
    DB-->>API: PrepSessionWithMessages
    API-->>Frontend: Session + message history
    Frontend-->>User: Chat UI (SessionChatView)

    Note over User,LLM: Each user message: unified chat turn (production UI)
    User->>Frontend: Type message and send
    Frontend->>API: POST /api/v1/sessions/{id}/chat { content, prefer_difficulty? }
    API->>DB: INSERT Message (USER / ANSWER)
    Note right of API: Agent: classify, tutor reply, first question, evaluate_answer, next question — calls LLM as needed
    API->>LLM: Completions (question / feedback / redirect / title / summary)
    LLM-->>API: Model outputs
    API->>DB: INSERT Message(s) (QUESTION, FEEDBACK, …)
    DB-->>API: persisted rows
    API-->>Frontend: ChatTurnPayload { new_messages[] }
    Frontend-->>User: Append messages in thread (scores in FEEDBACK meta when present)
